# INTRODUCTION TO HTML (UNDERSTANDING-FIRST NOTES)

---

# What is HTML?

HTML stands for:

```text
H → Hyper
T → Text
M → Markup
L → Language
```

HTML is the standard language used to create the structure of web pages.

It tells the browser:

```text
"What content exists on the page?"
```

Examples:

```text
• Headings
• Paragraphs
• Images
• Links
• Tables
• Forms
• Buttons
```

---

# The Biggest Misconception

Many beginners think:

```text
HTML is a programming language.
```

This is FALSE.

HTML is a:

```text
Markup Language
```

because it does NOT contain programming logic like:

```text
if statements
loops
functions
algorithms
```

Its job is simply to describe content.

---

