# Why Do We Need HTML?

Suppose browsers only received plain text.

Example:

```text
Welcome to my website
Click here
My image
```

How would the browser know:

```text
Which text is a heading?
Which is a paragraph?
Which is a button?
Which is an image?
```

It cannot.

HTML provides meaning.

Example:

```html
<h1>Welcome to my website</h1>

<p>This is my first website.</p>

<button>Click Here</button>
```

Now the browser understands the purpose of each piece of content.

---

# How Does HTML Work?

Flow:

```text
Developer writes HTML

        ↓

Browser reads HTML

        ↓

Browser interprets tags

        ↓

Browser renders webpage
```

Example:

HTML:

```html
<h1>Hello</h1>
```

Browser displays:

```text
Hello
```

as a large heading.

---

# What is a Tag?

HTML is built using tags.

A tag tells the browser what something is.

Example:

```html
<h1>Hello</h1>
```

Here:

```text
<h1>   → Opening tag

Hello  → Content

</h1>  → Closing tag
```

Visualization:

```text
<Tag Name>

Content

</Tag Name>
```

---

# HTML Element

An HTML element consists of:

```text
Opening Tag
+
Content
+
Closing Tag
```

Example:

```html
<p>I love HTML.</p>
```

Element:

```text
<p>           Opening Tag

I love HTML. Content

</p>          Closing Tag
```

---

# Common HTML Tags

## Heading Tags

Used for titles.

```html
<h1>Main Heading</h1>

<h2>Sub Heading</h2>

<h3>Small Heading</h3>

...

<h6>Smallest Heading</h6>
```

Hierarchy:

```text
h1 → Most Important

↓

h6 → Least Important
```

---

## Paragraph Tag

Used for normal text.

```html
<p>This is a paragraph.</p>
```

Browser displays:

```text
This is a paragraph.
```

---

## Link Tag

Used to navigate.

```html
<a href="https://example.com">
    Visit Website
</a>
```

Browser displays:

```text
Visit Website
```

Clicking opens the URL.

---

## Image Tag

Used to display images.

```html
<img src="cat.jpg" alt="Cat">
```

Unlike most tags:

```text
No closing tag.
```

---

## Button Tag

Creates buttons.

```html
<button>Submit</button>
```

Displays:

```text
[ Submit ]
```

---

# HTML Attributes

Attributes provide extra information.

Syntax:

```html
<tag attribute="value">
```

Example:

```html
<a href="https://google.com">
```

Here:

```text
href      → Attribute

https://google.com → Value
```

Meaning:

```text
This link should open Google.
```

---

# Basic HTML Document Structure

Every HTML page follows a structure.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>

<head>
    <title>My Website</title>
</head>

<body>

    <h1>Hello World</h1>

    <p>My first webpage.</p>

</body>

</html>
```

---

# Understanding Each Part

## 1. <!DOCTYPE html>

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
```

Purpose:

```text
Tells browser:

"This document uses HTML5."
```

Without it:

```text
Browser may enter compatibility mode.
```

---

## 2. <html>

```html
<html>
```

Purpose:

```text
Root element.

Everything lives inside it.
```

Visualization:

```text
HTML Document
│
└── html
```

---

## 3. <head>

```html
<head>
```

Contains information ABOUT the webpage.

Examples:

```text
Title
Metadata
CSS Links
JavaScript Links
SEO Information
```

Not visible to users.

---

## 4. <title>

```html
<title>My Website</title>
```

Purpose:

```text
Sets browser tab title.
```

Example:

Browser Tab:

```text
My Website
```

---

## 5. <body>

```html
<body>
```

Contains everything visible.

Examples:

```text
Headings
Paragraphs
Images
Buttons
Tables
Forms
Videos
```

Visualization:

```text
body
│
├─ Heading
├─ Paragraph
├─ Image
└─ Button
```

