# Browser Interpretation

HTML Code:

```html
<h1>Hello</h1>

<p>Welcome to HTML.</p>
```

Browser sees:

```text
This is a heading.

This is a paragraph.
```

Then renders:

```text
HELLO

Welcome to HTML.
```

---

# HTML Is Like a Skeleton

Imagine a human body.

```text
Skeleton  → HTML

Skin      → CSS

Movement  → JavaScript
```

Without HTML:

```text
No structure exists.
```

Without CSS:

```text
Ugly but functional.
```

Without JavaScript:

```text
Static webpage.
```

