# Real Example

HTML:

```html
<h1>Online Store</h1>

<p>Best products available.</p>

<button>Buy Now</button>
```

Browser shows:

```text
ONLINE STORE

Best products available.

[ Buy Now ]
```

HTML simply describes:

```text
What exists.
```

---

# Important Facts

```text
• HTML is not a programming language.

• HTML is a markup language.

• HTML creates webpage structure.

• Browsers interpret HTML tags.

• Tags define content meaning.

• Attributes provide extra information.

• Every webpage has a basic HTML structure.

• HTML works together with CSS and JavaScript.
```

---

# Complete Mental Model

```text
User opens website
        ↓
Browser requests HTML file
        ↓
Server sends HTML
        ↓
Browser reads tags
        ↓
Creates DOM (Document Object Model)
        ↓
Applies CSS
        ↓
Executes JavaScript
        ↓
Displays webpage
```

---

# 30-Second Interview Summary

```text
HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language and is the standard language used to structure web pages.

It is not a programming language because it does not contain logic. Instead, it uses tags to describe content such as headings, paragraphs, images, links, and forms.

Browsers interpret HTML and render webpages. HTML provides structure, CSS provides styling, and JavaScript provides behavior.
```

